Post-Doctoral Researcher in Homotopy Type Theory / Category Theory / =
Type Theory / Homotopy Theory
Carnegie Mellon University / Philosophy Department=20

The research group in Homotopy Type Theory at Carnegie Mellon University =
seeks a Post-Doctoral Researcher, without teaching duties, for one =
academic year, with a possibility of renewal. =20
Position could begin as early as August 2017, or later.  Candidates =
should have a PhD and research experience in a relevant area and a =
desire to collaborate with the existing research group, which consists =
of several faculty members, postdocs, and graduate students.

Questions about the position may be directed to Steve Awodey, =
awodey@cmu.edu.
Candidates should submit a CV and a brief research statement to =
CMUPhilosophy@andrew.cmu.edu.

